column4: I need a skype-like but with webcam support, do you know any?
who do you need to be compatible with?
gnomemeeting is compatible with netmeeting, and it looks like they're solving the issues with NAT
but I need some without problems with NAT
who do you need to talk to?
with another person who is also behind NAT
can either of you get into the DMZ?
no, is a student dorm (not access to router)
if I could access I know what ports redirectr
you might be able to get a more bleeding edge build of gnomemeeting with more support for rendevous/zeroconf/upnp/blah
yes i know, I'll try to build a cvs version
other than that it sounds like you're out of luck: roll on IPv6
you're not in the same NAT-ed network or anything handy like that?
